<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment uc->pp = NULL is dead: within response_completed_callback the post-processor pointer is destroyed via MHD_destroy_post_processor(uc->pp) and immediately the whole UploadContext object uc is freed at the end of the function (free(uc)). No subsequent code observes uc->pp (and *req_cls is not updated), so setting the member to NULL has no effect on program behaviour — removing the single assignment would not change program behaviour. Therefore this operation constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
